Cross-Site Scripting was identifed on the web application. Using input forms, an attacker could store JavaScript within the web application that would execute on the end-userâ€™s browser.
This could be used to steal cookies and local data or redirect users to malicious web pages, as well as many other attack scenarios.
User input should be treated as unsafe and never be trusted. All data sent to the server should be sanitised on input and correctly encoded on output.